        </profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.01/4–645</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum for the President by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-08">April 8,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Our consultations with the nineteen other American Republics have been completed
                    and they are unanimous in their view that diplomatic relations should be resumed
                    immediately with the Argentine Government. We intend to announce at noon,
                    Monday, April 9, that we are taking the action contemplated in my message which
                    you approved on April 6. Parallel action is being taken by the other American
                    Republics.</p>
                <pb facs="0391" n="377" xml:id="pg_377"/>
                <p>Braden’s<note n="33" xml:id="d254fn33">Spruille Braden.</note> nomination as
                    Ambassador to the Argentine is being submitted to you for approval.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E. R. S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tettinius</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
